### Step 6.4: Generate Executive Summary Email

**What you're doing:** Creating the follow-up email to stakeholders summarizing findings.

**Email structure:**
1. Context (why you're writing)
2. Most important findings first
3. Supporting details
4. Next steps
5. Attachment reference

**Expected output:** Ready-to-send email text
```

```python
# Cell 18: Generate Executive Summary Email

from datetime import datetime

# Generate email content
email_subject = "Follow-Up: Impound Lien Loss Analysis - Key Findings & Recommendations"

email_body = f"""
Hi Team,

Thanks again for your time in our discussion on {datetime.now().strftime('%B %d, %Y')}. I'm writing to close out the follow-up items we discussed regarding the impound lien loss investigation.

‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ
KEY FINDINGS
‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ

1. DATA SCOPE CONFIRMATION
   ‚úì Confirmed: {TOTAL_CASES:,} cases analyzed (July 2024 - July 2025)
   ‚úì All cases are TRUE impound losses only (abandoned vehicles excluded)

2. FRAUD ASSESSMENT: NO EVIDENCE DETECTED
   ‚úì Repeat offender companies (7 total) target LOWER value vehicles
     - Repeat offenders: ${AVG_VALUE_REPEAT:,.0f} average
     - Portfolio benchmark: ${BENCHMARK_VALUE:,.0f} average  
     - Difference: {((AVG_VALUE_REPEAT - BENCHMARK_VALUE) / BENCHMARK_VALUE * 100):+.0f}%
   ‚úì This pattern rules out systematic targeting of high-value assets
   ‚úì Repeat offenses appear to be operational issues at high-volume facilities

3. COVERAGE GAP IDENTIFIED: 23% OPPORTUNITY
   ‚Ä¢ {COVERAGE_PCT:.0f}% of cases ({COVERED_CASES:,}) occur in states WITH verification coverage
   ‚Ä¢ {COVERAGE_GAP_PCT:.0f}% of cases ({UNCOVERED_CASES:,}) occur in states WITHOUT coverage
   ‚Ä¢ The {COVERAGE_GAP_PCT:.0f}% gap represents ~${UNCOVERED_EXPOSURE/1_000_000:.1f}M in annual controllable exposure
   ‚Ä¢ Top uncovered states: Texas ({len(df_impound[df_impound['state']=='TX'])if 'TX' in df_impound['state'].values else 'X'} cases), 
     Florida ({len(df_impound[df_impound['state']=='FL']) if 'FL' in df_impound['state'].values else 'X'} cases), 
     Illinois ({len(df_impound[df_impound['state']=='IL']) if 'IL' in df_impound['state'].values else 'X'} cases)

4. VERIFICATION PROCESS PERFORMANCE: STRONG WITH MINOR LEAKAGE
   ‚úì Process adherence: {VERIFICATION_RATE:.0f}% of eligible cases are verified (excellent)
   ‚úì Match success rate: {MATCH_SUCCESS_RATE:.0f}% (strong effectiveness)
   ‚ö† Slippage: {SLIPPAGE_RATE:.0f}% ({SLIPPAGE_CASES:,} cases) still slip through despite verification
   ‚Üí Root cause analysis needed to understand why these {SLIPPAGE_CASES:,} cases weren't prevented

5. REPEAT OFFENDER ANALYSIS
   ‚Ä¢ 7 companies with 3+ losses account for {REPEAT_OFFENDER_CASES:,} cases ({(REPEAT_OFFENDER_CASES/TOTAL_CASES)*100:.0f}% of total)
   ‚Ä¢ Pattern is consistent with high-volume operators, not malicious activity
   ‚Ä¢ {repeat_covered_pct:.0f}% of repeat offender cases are in covered states vs {repeat_uncovered_pct:.0f}% uncovered

‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ
RECOMMENDATIONS (Prioritized by ROI)
‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ

üéØ PRIORITY 1: Expand Verification Coverage to Uncovered States
   Impact: {UNCOVERED_CASES:,} cases/year (~${UNCOVERED_EXPOSURE/1_000_000:.1f}M)
   Timeline: 6-9 months
   Next Step: Meet with ADD123/Ventiling to discuss state expansion feasibility

üìã PRIORITY 2: Root Cause Analysis of {SLIPPAGE_RATE:.0f}% No-Match Cases  
   Impact: {SLIPPAGE_CASES:,} cases/year (~${(SLIPPAGE_CASES * AVG_IMPOUND_VALUE)/1_000_000:.2f}M)
   Timeline: 2-4 weeks
   Next Step: Pull detailed records for all {SLIPPAGE_CASES:,} no-match cases and interview titles team

‚ö° PRIORITY 3: Establish Direct Relationships with Repeat Offenders
   Impact: ~{int(REPEAT_OFFENDER_CASES * 0.3):,} cases/year (30% reduction estimate)
   Timeline: 1-2 months  
